# Cursor Rules — Admin Panel (Laravel + Vue 3)

## 0) Goal & Scope
- Build ONLY the **Admin Panel** for the restaurant system.
- Admin is inside the Laravel project using **Vue 3 + Vite**.
- Admin must manage: **Orders, Categories, Menu Items, Offers, Restaurant Settings, Staff Users**.
- Customer Next.js is OUT of scope for now.

---

## 1) Architecture Rules
- Vue 3 is a SPA mounted inside Laravel (`/admin`).
- All data comes from Laravel API endpoints under `/api/admin/*`.
- Use **Sanctum** authentication for admin routes.
- Every API request must enforce **restaurant_id scoping** (multi-restaurant safe).
- Never expose data from one restaurant to another (MUST).

---

## 2) Folder & Naming Rules (Vue 3)
- Use clean module structure:
  - `src/admin/pages/*` (route pages)
  - `src/admin/components/*` (reusable UI)
  - `src/admin/modules/*` (feature modules: orders/menu/offers/settings)
  - `src/admin/stores/*` (Pinia)
  - `src/admin/services/*` (API clients)
  - `src/admin/router/*` (routes + guards)
  - `src/admin/types/*` (TypeScript types/interfaces)

- Naming:
  - Pages: `OrdersIndex.vue`, `OrdersShow.vue`, `MenuItemsIndex.vue`
  - Components: `DataTable.vue`, `FormField.vue`, `StatusBadge.vue`
  - Stores: `useOrdersStore.ts`, `useMenuStore.ts`

---

## 3) UI/UX Rules
- Must be responsive (desktop first, usable on mobile).
- Use consistent layout: Sidebar + Topbar + Main content.
- Every list page must have: Search, Filters, Pagination, Empty state, Loading state.
- Every form must have: Inline validation messages, Disabled submit while saving, Toast success/error feedback.
- Deleting anything requires confirm dialog.

---

## 4) Admin Pages (MUST Build)
### Core
- **Dashboard** — overview widgets
- **Orders** — list with status tabs + search + filters; order details page/drawer; status change actions
- **Menu** — Categories CRUD + reorder + active toggle; Menu Items CRUD + image upload + availability toggle + featured toggle
- **Offers** — CRUD + active toggle + scheduling (start/end)
- **Restaurant Settings** — branding, contact, hours, delivery rules
- **Staff/Users** (Owner only) — create/disable staff, assign role

---

## 5) Data & Security Rules (Laravel API)
- Use Form Requests for every create/update endpoint.
- Use Policies/Gates for every resource: `restaurant_id` match is required.
- Use Resources/Transformers for responses (no raw models).
- Use Pagination for list endpoints.
- Never return hidden/sensitive fields (tokens, passwords).

---

## 6) Orders Workflow Rules
- Order status enum: `pending -> accepted -> preparing -> out_for_delivery -> delivered`; `cancelled` allowed from `pending/accepted` only (unless owner overrides).
- Every status change must be recorded in `order_status_logs` table OR `orders.status_updated_at` + audit fields.
- Order details must show: subtotal, delivery_fee, discount, grand_total.
- Orders list must show: created time, customer phone, total, current status.

---

## 7) Image Upload Rules (Menu Items + Offers + Branding)
- Single upload flow: validate file type (jpg/png/webp), limit size (e.g. 2MB), store in `storage/app/public`, return public URL.
- UI must show preview before save where possible.
- Always handle missing images gracefully.

---

## 8) API Client Rules (Vue)
- Centralize API calls in `services/api.ts`.
- Attach auth cookies/headers properly for Sanctum.
- Standardize error handling: show toast error with message from API; fallback generic message if missing.
- Do NOT duplicate API logic inside components.

---

## 9) State Management Rules (Pinia)
- Use Pinia for: auth user + role, orders list filters/pagination, menu items/categories state.
- Do NOT store huge datasets in memory; rely on pagination.
- Always keep URL query params in sync with filters for list pages.

---

## 10) Routing & Guards Rules
- Admin routes under `/admin/*`.
- Unauthenticated users redirect to `/admin/login`.
- Role-based access: Owner-only routes for Settings (certain sections), Staff management.
- Use a global route guard that checks auth state.

---

## 11) Coding Standards
- TypeScript everywhere in Vue.
- No `any` unless absolutely necessary; if used, explain with comment.
- Components must be small and reusable (avoid 800-line pages).
- Keep logic in stores/services; components focus on UI.

---

## 12) Quality Checklist (Before Marking Any Admin Feature Complete)
- [ ] API endpoints exist and are secured by policy
- [ ] Vue page exists and is accessible via routing
- [ ] Search, filter, pagination implemented (where list exists)
- [ ] Validation errors display correctly
- [ ] Success/error toast feedback works
- [ ] Empty/loading states exist
- [ ] Mobile layout tested
- [ ] No cross-restaurant data access possible

---

## 13) Commit Rules
- Commit after each meaningful feature with conventional commits, e.g.:
  - `feat(admin): orders list + filters`
  - `feat(admin): order details + status updates`
  - `feat(admin): menu categories CRUD`
  - `feat(admin): menu items CRUD + upload`
  - `feat(admin): offers CRUD`
  - `feat(admin): restaurant settings`
  - `feat(admin): staff management`
- No "WIP" commits on main branch.
